The paper deals with algorithmic problems in algebraic geometry, specifically the Noether Normalization Lemma. Therefore, cs.AG (Algebraic Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses complexity theory and efficient algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.SC (Symbolic Computation). The use of randomized and deterministic algorithms implies that it could be relevant to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as well.
